r. Ray florets 0. Disc florets 10–22; corollas 9–11 mm. Cypselae brownish, narrowly oblong, 5–6 mm, densely hairy; pappi tan, 8–10 mm.</description><phenology>summer</phenology><phenology>jun</phenology><phenology>jul</phenology><phenology>aug</phenology><phenology>fall</phenology><phenology>sep</phenology><phenology>oct</phenology><phenology>nov</phenology><habitat>dry, stony slopes</habitat><elevation>ca. 2300 m;</elevation><us_distribution>Mont.</us_distribution><us_distribution>Wyo.</us_distribution></treatment>
